ntaining the exact replacement from `git show HEAD:path`. Using Python will make this easier, as I won't need to touch the working tree. After that, I’ll get the blob with `git hash-object -w temp` and update the index using `git update-index --cacheinfo`. I’ll just ensure the working tree stays intact. Let's get started on the script!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_V0OaJB3B5oOAZGyo1Hc0fl0X|fc_08c74b9fb34b62d60169f02b8f955481959f566f4320581b22", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport subprocess\n\nrepo_path = 'tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.jr/jackson-jr-objects/2.21.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json'\nhead = subprocess.check_output(['git', 'show', f'HEAD:{repo_path}'], text=True)\nold = '''    {\n      \"condition\" : {\n        \"typeReached\" : \"com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.impl.BeanPropertyReader\"\n      },\n      \"type\" : \"com_fasterxml_jackson_jr.jackson_jr_objects.BeanConstructorsDynamicAccessTest$DefaultConstructorBean\",\n      \"fields\" : [\n        {\n          \"name\" : \"id\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\" : \"name\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"condition\" : {\n        \"typeReached\" : \"com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.impl.BeanReader\"\n      },\n      \"type\" : \"com_fasterxml_jackson_jr.jackson_jr_objects.BeanConstructorsDynamicAccessTest$DefaultConstructorBean\",\n      \"methods\" : [\n        {\n          \"name\" : \"<init>\",\n          \"parameterTypes\" : [ ]\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"condition\" : {\n        \"typeReached\" : \"com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.impl.ValueReaderLocator\"\n      },\n      \"type\" : \"com_fasterxml_jackson_jr.jackson_jr_objects.BeanConstructorsDynamicAccessTest$DefaultConstructorBean\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"condition\" : {\n        \"typeReached\" : \"com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.impl.BeanPropertyReader\"\n      },\n      \"type\" : \"com_fasterxml_jackson_jr.jackson_j